ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W4_StudentCourseRegistrationApp

Class Name: StudentCourseRegistrationApp

Difficulty: Level 3.5 — File-Based Object-Oriented Application

Estimated Time: 75–100 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 88 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Create a console-based course registration system that processes student course requests,
handles approval, waitlist, rejection, and saves/loads registration records using files.

Program Flow
The main method creates students, courses, registration requests, a RegistrationCenter,
and a RegistrationFileManager. The center processes the requests, prints a summary,
and the file manager saves and reads the results.

Class Responsibilities
StudentCourseRegistrationApp: runs the sample scenario.
Student: stores student identity.
Course: manages capacity and enrolled students.
RegistrationRequest: stores one request and its status.
RegistrationCenter: coordinates validation and registration processing.
RegistrationFileManager: handles file output and input.
InvalidRegistrationException: represents invalid registration data.

Object Collaboration
The center receives requests, asks Course objects about capacity and duplicate enrollment,
updates each RegistrationRequest status, and passes processed records to the file manager.
